# Sajtmaskin Terminology

## Site layers (top to bottom)

| Layer | What it is | URL pattern |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **Vercel** | Hosting platform. Deploys, domains, env vars, CDN. | vercel.com |
| **Sajtmaskin** | Our app. Own code-generation engine (default), manages projects, users, deploy flow. | sajtmaskin.se |
| **v0** (soft-deprecated) | v0 Platform API + `v0-sdk` still used for templates, registry, zip, deploy-related calls — **not** for builder codegen streams. Optional `V0_FALLBACK_BUILDER` (affirmative only) prefers v0-hosted `demoUrl` in preview when both sandbox and v0 URLs exist. | v0.dev, *.vusercontent.net |
| **Demo sites** | User-generated sites. Built by own engine, previewed in-app (full Next.js stack in iframe when that path is active), deployed to Vercel. In conversation, **demo URL** often means this preview/deploy URL for the user site — not the legacy v0-hosted preview. | *.vercel.app, preview/sandbox URL, or custom domain |

## Pages in our app

### Start page (`/`)

The landing page with 4 entry modes shown as tabs/cards:

| Mode | Code name | Component | What it does |
|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| **Analyserad** (Wizard) | `wizard` | `PromptWizardModalV2` | 5-step guided questionnaire that builds a detailed prompt |
| **Template** (v0-templates) | `category` | `TemplateGallery` | Browse **v0-templates** from `src/lib/templates/`, pick a starting point. Landing tab id `template` (legacy query/deep links: `kategori`, `mall`). |
| **Audit** | `audit` | `SiteAuditSection` + `AuditModal` | Analyze an existing website URL, show improvement suggestions |
| **Fritext** (Freeform) | `freeform` | `PromptInput` | Type a free-text description directly |

All 4 modes lead to the **builder** via `/builder?buildMethod=<mode>&...`

Important language rule:
- Use **`Fritext`** in Swedish product/UI copy.
- Use **`freeform`** as the canonical code/query/API value.

### Builder (`/builder`)

The main workspace where the user iterates on their site:
- Left panel: chat interface (prompt, AI responses, version history)
- Right panel: live preview (iframe or app preview route)
- Header: model selection, scaffold mode, custom instructions, deploy button

### Admin (`/admin`)

Internal dashboard with tabs: Database, Environment, Analytics, Prompts.

## Key concepts

### Three-word cheat sheet (scaffold / dossier / artifact)

Use these **one meaning per word** in docs and agent answers (details below still apply):

| Word | Means | Typical location |
|------|--------|------------------|
| **Scaffold** | Runtime **starting point** the generator can use (internal starters). | `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/` |
| **Dossier** | Curated **research package** about an external template (not the live codegen base). | `research/external-templates/.../dossiers/` |
| **Artifact** | **Generated data** consumed by code (JSON, embeddings, ranked lists). | `src/lib/gen/template-library/`, `scaffold-research.generated.json`, etc. |

Folder-level narrative: [`docs/architecture/structure-and-terminology.md`](../../docs/architecture/structure-and-terminology.md). Cursor vs product workflows: [`docs/contributing/agent-workflows.md`](../../docs/contributing/agent-workflows.md).

### v0-templates, scaffolds, and Vercel mall (research)

Do **not** use the old “operational lanes” triad. One mental model:

| Layer | Where | Role |
|-------|--------|------|
| **Runtime generation** | `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`, matcher, stream, preview/deploy | **Scaffold-driven** — not driven by gallery rows at generation time. |
| **v0-templates** | `src/lib/templates/`, `TemplateGallery` | Product browse/search; `buildMethod=category`; landing **Template** tab. |
| **Vercel mall** (research) | `research/external-templates/`, dossiers, `src/lib/gen/template-library/`, scaffold research JSON | Curated reference + artifacts that **inform scaffolds** and ranking — not the landing Template label. |

#### Builder picker **Mall** / **Mallar** vs **Vercel-mall** (research)

These sound alike in Swedish but are **different products**:

| Surface | Code / location | What the user sees | Runtime / source |
|--------|------------------|--------------------|------------------|
| **Mall** tab in the builder | `UnifiedElementPicker` → `activeTab === "mall"` → `TemplateGallery` | Previews and starts from **v0 community templates** (gallery IDs in `src/lib/templates/`). | **v0 Platform** — `v0.chats.init({ type: "template", templateId })` and v0-hosted previews where applicable. |
| **Vercel Template** / **Vercel-mall** (research lane) | `vercel.com/templates` intake, `e2e/vercel-templates/` (tracked Playwright spec), `research/external-templates/`; legacy `vercel_templates_levels/` may exist locally (ignored) | **Not** exposed as this gallery. Feeds **raw discovery → dossiers → generated artifacts → scaffold research**. | **Offline research** and curation scripts — **not** the builder Mall tab. |

Rules of thumb:

- If the user opened **Mall / Mallar** inside the builder, they are interacting with **v0-templates** only.
- **Vercel mallar** (public catalog) are how we **learn and rank** external starters to improve **runtime scaffolds** and enrichment — users do **not** pick those rows from the Mall tab today.
- Do not describe the Mall tab as “Vercel templates” or imply it lists `vercel.com/templates`.

| Term | Swedish / UI | Meaning |
|------|--------------|---------|
| **v0-templates** | **Template** / **Templates** (nav) | Gallery entries from `src/lib/templates/`; not the runtime codegen base. |
| **Runtime scaffold** | `grundmall` | Internal starters in `src/lib/gen/scaffolds/`; own-engine generation base (auto / manual / off). |
| **Vercel mall** | disambiguate when needed | Vercel ecosystem + **reference dossiers** + **generated research artifacts** — not the v0-templates tab. |
| **Vercel Template** | `extern Vercel-template` | One public starter from vercel.com/templates. |
| **Reference dossier** | `referensdossier` | Curated package under `.../dossiers/`; feeds build scripts, not runtime directly. |
| **Generated research artifact** | — | Committed JSON/embeddings in `template-library/`, `scaffold-research.generated.json`; consumed for ranking / enrichment. |
| **Raw discovery** | `rå upptäckt` | Noisy scrape under `raw-discovery/`; gitignored. |
| **Multi-tenant** | `delad plattform` | One app serving many tenants. |
| **Multi-project** | `separata kundprojekt` | One Vercel project per customer site. |

Rules: **scaffold** vs **v0-template** — never call runtime scaffolds plain “templates”. **Mall** in the **builder picker** = **v0-templates** (v0 runtime), **not** Vercel.com catalog rows. **Vercel mall** (research) → dossiers and scaffolds, not the Mall tab inventory. Dossiers are research input, not a second scaffold registry; only **generated artifacts** matter at runtime. Do not mix this block with **builder model lanes** (below).

### Builder model lanes (user-facing)

When discussing model selection inside the builder, use this lane vocabulary:

| Lane | Swedish label | What it controls | Where user picks it |
|------|---------------|------------------|---------------------|
| **Model lane** | `bygg-lane` | Main generation model for the actual build/refine stream | `Byggmodell` (`modelId` / `modelTier`) |
| **Product lane** | `prompt-lane` | Prompt-assist model used before build (rewrite/brief/spec support) | `Förbättra` + `Djup brief` (UI) |
| **Polish lane** | `billig/snabb/latt lane` | Low-cost text-only rewrite of the prompt input | `Skriv om` (`SAJTMASKIN_POLISH_MODEL`) |
| **Thinking flag** | `tankeflagga` | Extra reasoning behavior in generation metadata | `Resonemang` (UI) |

Important rules:
- Do NOT mix up **scaffold / Vercel-mall research** concerns with `builder model lanes`.
- `Anthropic` can be selected in the **model lane** (build profile `anthropic`) and also in the **product lane** (`anthropic/*` assist model strings).
- The **Anthropic-jämförelse** preset (UI; code may still say `AnthropicCompare`) aligns both model lane and product lane to Anthropic for apples-to-apples comparison.
- **Resonemang** is not a lane and does not replace model or product lane selection.

### Common chat aliases

Treat common misspellings and spoken-style aliases as canonical platform names:

| Alias in chat | Canonical term |
|---------------|----------------|
| `Varicell`, `Vericell` | `Vercel` |
| `Veenol`, `Venol` | `v0` |

When answering, prefer canonical names (`Vercel`, `v0`) even if user writes an alias.

### Embeddings vs semantics (English ↔ Swedish)

These English words look similar but mean different things. Match Swedish copy to the right concept:

| English (code, logs, filenames) | Meaning | Swedish in product/admin UI | Do not confuse with |
|---------------------------------|---------|------------------------------|---------------------|
| **semantics**, **semantic HTML** | Correct HTML elements and roles (structure, a11y) | **semantik**, **semantisk HTML**, **semantiska element** | ML “semantic” |
| **semantic search** (docs, KB, templates) | Similarity search using vectors | **semantisk sökning**; when clarifying for admins: **sökning med vektorinbäddningar** | HTML semantics |
| **embedding** / **embeddings** | Numeric vector from an embedding model (e.g. OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small`) | **inbäddning** / **inbäddningar** (optional: *embeddings* in parens for devs) | HTML semantics |

Identifiers (`semantic-search.ts`, API paths) stay English; Swedish for UI copy only. **Tailwind semantic tokens** (`bg-primary`, …) = **tematokens** / design tokens — not HTML semantics and not ML embeddings.

### Orchestrator terms

Use this vocabulary consistently for automation work:

- `orchestrator run` - the full dated execution folder under `.cursor/orchestrator/run/`
- `orchestrator agent` - the coordinator that plans, delegates, validates, and performs minor fixes
- `run roadmap` - the per-run `ROADMAP.md`
- `track plan` - an intermediate tier-2 plan for one broader workstream inside an orchestrator run
- `agent log` - a per-workload execution note written by the delegated agent
- `final sweep` - the closing cleanup and audit pass for dead code, ghost routes, stale files, and doc drift

Treat `/orchestrator` and `/automation` as the compact startup aliases for the
orchestrator-run system.

### Generation pipeline

The own engine generation flow:

1. **Prompt assist** (optional) — rewrites/briefs the user prompt before generation
2. **Prompt orchestration** — budget/strategy for the message (`direct`, `summarize`, `phase_plan_build_polish`)
3. **Scaffold resolution** — auto-match, manual pick, or off
4. **Context orchestration** (`orchestrate.ts`) — builds scaffold context, route plan, capability inference, contract inference
5. **System prompt** (`system-prompt.ts`) — STATIC_CORE (~6-8K tokens, cached) + dynamic context (custom instructions, build intent, scaffold, brief, theme, references, KB matches, template references)
6. **Generation stream** — own engine via OpenAI, or v0 fallback
7. **Post-generation** — autofix, esbuild validation, URL expansion, file parsing, scaffold merge

### Custom instructions

Two tiers in `src/lib/builder/defaults.ts`:

- **CORE_CUSTOM_INSTRUCTIONS** — always active: tech stack, shadcn setup, language, accessibility
- **EXTENDED_CUSTOM_INSTRUCTIONS** — only when scaffold is `off`: design system execution, component usage, Tailwind, visual identity, layout, motion, images, Figma workflow

Selection: `getDefaultCustomInstructions(scaffoldMode)`:
- scaffold `auto` or `manual` → CORE only (scaffold + STATIC_CORE covers design)
- scaffold `off` → CORE + EXTENDED (no scaffold, needs full design guidance)

The user can edit these in the builder header dialog. `isDefaultCustomInstructions()` detects manual edits.

### Research pipeline (order)

`raw discovery` → (optional raw datasets) → **reference dossier** → **generated research artifacts** → consumed for search/ranking; **runtime scaffold** remains the codegen base. Paths: `docs/architecture/structure-and-terminology.md`.

### Build method (`BuildMethod`)

How the user entered the builder. One of:
`wizard` | `category` | `audit` | `freeform` | `kostnadsfri`

### Engine path naming

- **`own-engine`** and **`egen motor`** are the **same** product concept: the default Sajtmaskin code-generation path (not v0 fallback).
- Use **`own-engine`** as the canonical technical string in metadata, routes, and logs.
- Use **`egen motor`** only as the Swedish display label in UI copy.

### Build intent (`BuildIntent`)

What the user wants to build:
- `website` - standard multi-page website (default)
- `app` - interactive app with logic/flows
- `template` - compact 1-2 page scope (UI label **Kompakt** — not “Mall”, to avoid clashing with **Vercel mall** / scaffold vocabulary)

### Internal theme vs Figma vs v0 design system

These concepts are also different and should NOT be mixed:

| Term | Variable/type name | Meaning | Scope |
|------|--------------------|---------|-------|
| **Internal theme preset** | `designTheme` / `themeColors` | Sajtmaskin's own theme preset and derived semantic colors used to steer the own engine's output. | Internal builder + own engine |
| **Figma reference** | attachment with `purpose: "figma-reference"` | A visual reference used to guide hierarchy, spacing, composition, and styling. Not a reusable component system by itself. | Prompt/reference concept |
| **v0 Design System** | `designSystemId` / `v0DesignSystemId` | External registry-backed design system for v0 — not the same as `designTheme` or a Figma file. Prefer `v0DesignSystemId` in code talk. | External v0 integration |

Do not call **`designTheme`** a “design system” without qualifier; Figma ≠ registry-backed `designSystemId`.

### Project

A sajtmaskin project that groups chats, versions, and deployments together.
Stored in our database. Has an `appProjectId` (ours) and optionally a
`v0ProjectId` (legacy, from v0 fallback era).

### Chat

A conversation in the builder. Each chat produces versions. With own engine
the chat is stored locally; with v0 fallback it maps to a v0 chat ID.

### Version

A snapshot of generated code from one generation turn. Contains files
(the actual React/Next.js code) and optionally a preview URL.

### Preview

**User-site preview** (own engine): generated Next.js project is shown in-app
(iframe / dedicated preview surface). Product language may use **demo URL** for
this URL even though it is not the old v0 preview host.

**v0-hosted demo URL** (`*.vusercontent.net`): may appear as `demoUrl` on a version.
When `V0_FALLBACK_BUILDER` is affirmative, the builder can **prefer** this URL
over sandbox in the preview iframe; codegen remains own-engine.

**Degraded preview env:** placeholder values for third-party keys so preview
can start without real integrations; canonical KEY=value fragment
`config/ai_models/40-generated-site-integration-placeholders.env.txt` (see
`config/ai_models/manifest.json`), policy text `config/user_degraded_env.txt`.
Generated sites should degrade gracefully (mock / no-op) per
`config/prompt-static/11-behavioral-rules.md`.

The **Sandbox** (`@vercel/sandbox` via `SandboxModal`) is opt-in for testing
server-side behavior before deploying.

### Deployment

When the user clicks "Deploy":
1. Fetch the version's files
2. Process images (upload to Vercel Blob if needed)
3. Create a Vercel deployment via Vercel REST API
4. Return a permanent URL on the user's Vercel project

